what do you think the candle flickers as the clock winds the young princess sits on her bed as the shackles around her hands bind a death trap lies above her bed a mallet tied with rope just waiting to smash her head she waits for her prince to come but that's like waiting for the chatty to be mum she sees only one way to make it out of this alive she must escape and she has to be conniving the sun comes up on almost a perfect day but if she can't escape another night she awaits the evildoer leaves her for a fight she has to act quickly and take flight seeing that her shackles will never give she must find a tool to pry them loose no use another day is lost but the prince arrives to cut that cost he forces the binds off with one single move the princess asks him how he got there in time his reply was short and sweet i wound the clock back its ok i just think the last line is turned the clock back i don t think you can wind backwards as you would break the clock i think i agree with the other comments i think you should write a short story you are beginning to create imagery and i think you will develop faster through short story writing than free form poetry just my opinion Episodes of Lost (Season 1) The Amber Spyglass Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Aida (musical) The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe The Time Machine Sin City Shaggy dog story The Death Gate Cycle Anchor Professional wrestling throws Professional wrestling double-team maneuvers Tag Aladdin (1992 film) Johnny 5 Suplex Professional wrestling holds Escape from New York Naruto jutsu The Shining (film) Textile manufacturing Vegeta Piccolo (Dragon Ball) The Invisibles Ocean's Twelve Happy Tree Friends The Subtle Knife Ephesian Tale Sydney Riot of 1879 The Family from One End Street Blood Simple The Jazz Singer Taikyoku shogi The Empty Child The Marriage of Figaro The Inside The Lovely Bones Social rule Yom Kippur War Link (Legend of Zelda) Odyssey Theory of conduct Ben Johnson (athlete) Piccolo 